    "asOf": "2023-01-12",
    "date": "2023-01-25T17:53:54Z",
    "text": "Emergency Savings Accounts Act of 2023\n\nThis bill allows an individual taxpayer occupying a residence a deduction from gross income for up to $5,000 of amounts paid into such taxpayer's emergency savings account. The bill defines emergency savings account as an account established exclusively to pay the qualified disaster and public health emergency expenses of the account beneficiary.\n\nThe bill defines qualified disaster and public health emergency expenses as disaster mitigation expenses, disaster recovery expenses, public health emergency expenses, and unemployment-related expenses."
  },
